Move 2017_07_10_120054_user.php in database/migration
Move AuthController in app/Http/Controllers
Move AuthRoute in app/Http/Middleware
Move User.php In app/Models (or wherever your model directory is)

Add

`'authRoute'             => AuthRoute::class,`

in $routeMiddleware in app/Http/Kernel.php

And add the middleware authRoute in the Route files

public route to add

Route::get('/'.fitrans('routes.web.getLogin'), [
    'as'      => 'auth.login',
    'uses'    => 'AuthController@login'
]);

Route::post('/'.fitrans('routes.web.postLogin'), [
    'as'      => 'auth.loginStore',
    'uses'    => 'AuthController@loginStore'
]);

Route::get('/' . fitrans('routes.web.logout'), [
    'as'    => 'auth.logout',
    'uses'  => 'AuthController@logout'
]);

/**
 * Password recover
 */

Route::get('/' . fitrans('routes.web.password_recover'), [
    'as'    => 'auth.recoverPassword',
    'uses'  => 'AuthController@recoverPassword'
]);

Route::post('/' . fitrans('routes.web.password_recover'), [
    'as'    => 'auth.recoverPasswordStore',
    'uses'  => 'AuthController@recoverPasswordStore'
]);

Route::get('/' . fitrans('routes.web.password_renew').'/{recoverHash}', [
    'as'    => 'auth.renewPassword',
    'uses'  => 'AuthController@renewPassword'
]);

Route::post('/' . fitrans('routes.web.password_renew'), [
    'as'    => 'auth.renewPasswordStore',
    'uses'  => 'AuthController@renewPasswordStore'
]);

Move the views in Auth/ to the right folder and update them (also the extend of the Layouts)
